--[[
	Dorn's Weapon Tooltip

	Adds a per-ammo damage breakdown to weapon inventory tooltips and the
	weapon details popup (no LTX edits, all values read live). Renders below
	the flavor description via ui_dorn_weapon_tooltip.xml: the entire layout AND all static text live in the
	XML; the script only fills the dynamic number cells (each number is its own
	cell) and shows/hides rows. No icons - the type label carries the color.

	    DAMAGE:              vs Torso                              vs Head
	    Type  AP Min Lgt Lgt+ Mid Mid+ Hvy Hvy+ Exo Max  Min Lgt Mid Hvy Max
	    AP    51  ..  ..   ..  ..   ..  ..   ..  ..  ..   ..  ..  ..  ..  ..
	    FMJ   20  ..  ..   ..  ..   ..  ..   ..  ..  ..   ..  ..  ..  ..  ..

	where
	    AP <n>    = ammo k_ap x 1000 (matches the ammo's own info card),
	    columns   = named prevalent NPC bone-armor floats (combat_ap >= armor).
	                Failed-pen chip uses the average hit_fraction for that
	                exact armor only.

	One row per ammo round (Type label from AMMO_TYPE_SHORT map; unknown = ????).
	Type label color from AMMO_TYPE_COLOR (fallback grey).
	AP column grey-to-orange. Shift columns via XML.

	This script is prefixed zz_ on purpose: G.A.M.M.A. Accurate Defense Values
	rebuilds utils_ui.stats_table["weapon"] wholesale in ish_item_stats'
	on_game_start (and on difficulty change), which would wipe our re-enabled
	Damage row. Loading last (zz_) means our on_game_start / on_console_execute
	run after theirs, so the row sticks.

	Two optional MCM settings:

	1. show_damage_table - per-ammo DAMAGE panel below the description (on by default).

	2. column_headers - "names" (Min/Lgt/...) or "raw" (0.011/0.075/...).

	3. ammo_order - "damage" (dmg desc, AP asc), "ap" (AP desc), or
	   "default" (same order as tooltip ammo icons / ammo_class).

	4. calc_range - assumed distance in meters for damage math (0-200, default 20).
	   drop_range - Bullet Drop distance (100-2000, default 200).

	5. use_condition_table / use_condition_stats - when on, apply CQC
	   barrel-condition factors to the damage table / slash damage stats
	   (off = assume 100%).

	6. apply_silencer - when on (default), multiply stalker AP and damage by
	   CQC's 1.07 if a silencer is attached or the weapon has an integrated
	   suppressor. Mutant hits do not use this in live CQC.

	7. show_hit_power / show_stalker_damage / show_mutant_damage - Hit Power,
	   DMG vs Stalkers, and DMG vs Mutants rows (each on by default).

	8. show_accuracy / show_handling / show_reliability / show_recoil /
	   show_muzzle_velocity - base Momopate/vanilla rows (each on by default).

	9. Companion rows (MCM keys keep old names for saved settings):
	   show_base_spread = Dispersion, show_movement_spread = Move Spread,
	   show_weapon_wear = Bullet Wear, show_burst_control, show_bullet_drop.
	   Placement via stat_row_placement.

	10. stat_row_placement - "inline" (under related base row) or "after"
	   (Hit Power / DMG rows / companion rows as a block after Recoil Control).

	Development: rangefinder MCM toggle shows crosshair distance via DORN.dbg overlay.
]]

local MOD_ID = "dorn_weapon_tooltip"
local DORN_COMMON_VERSION = "dorn_common_c62f913d" -- managed by sync-dorn-common.sh, do not hand-edit

local DORN

